<dl id="n10076f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10076f">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10076f"> 76(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> atrament <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n10076f"><li>FW 452.03 </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/lexqA.htm#n10076f">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/l39qA.htm#n10076f">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n10076f">MS BL 47482b-29v</ms> </li><li>JJA 57:060 <a name="qA2d" href="../../ff/fdra/qda.htm#qA2d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/q/qa2d.htm#n10076f">Draft: III&sect;2A.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Nous voudrions savoir avec plus de pr&eacute;cision &agrave; quelle &eacute;poque de l&apos;histoire des Perses appartient un fait bien curieux, attest&eacute; par le savant polygraphe Juste Lipse. Que l&apos;on employ&acirc;t au transport des messages le cheval, le chameau, le mulet, l&apos;&acirc;ne d&apos;Orient, renomm&eacute; pour sa vitesse, l&apos;homme lui-m&ecirc;me, dress&eacute; &agrave; la course, rien de plus ordinaire; mais voil&agrave; qu&apos;on transportait des hirondelles loin, bien loin du nid o&ugrave; elles &eacute;taient n&eacute;es, du nid o&ugrave; elles avaient couv&eacute;; l&agrave;, on peignait sur leurs plumes certains signes, au moyen d&apos;ocre, d&apos;<mark>atrament</mark>, ou d&apos;autres teintures, puis on les rendait &agrave; la libert&eacute;. <font color="green">[We would like to know with more precision at what time of Persian history something happened that is attested by the polymath Justus Lipsius. That we use horses, camels, mules, oriental donkeys renowned for their speed to carry messages, even man himself, that is normal; but how is that they transported swallows from the nest where they were born; there messages were painted on their wings with ochre or ink, or other paints, and then one let them go]</font> <small> Arthur de Rothschild, <a name="ARHD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ARHD"><cite title="source">Histoire de la poste</cite></a> (1876) [24]</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Atrament: blacking, ink. </mm> </dd></dl>
